  nodes:
  - nodeID: L2_Entrance
    markerName: ImageTarget_L2_Entrance
    floor: 2
    worldPosition: {x: 0, y: 0}
    displayLabel: "Level 2 \u2013 Entrance"
    isStairNode: 0
    linkedStairNodeID: 
    visualDescription: Glass sliding doors and security turnstiles at the entrance.
      Reception desk with computer monitors on the right. Linoleum floor tiles. Directory
      sign on the left wall listing floor contents.
  - nodeID: L2_SectionA
    markerName: ImageTarget_L2_SectionA
    floor: 2
    worldPosition: {x: 5, y: 0}
    displayLabel: "Level 2 \u2013 Section A (Computing)"
    isStairNode: 0
    linkedStairNodeID: 
    visualDescription: Metal shelving units with blue spine labels in the 000-099
      Dewey range (Computing and Information Science). Cable management trays visible
      on the floor. Large window on the south wall. End-cap display with technology
      titles.
  - nodeID: L2_SectionB
    markerName: ImageTarget_L2_SectionB
    floor: 2
    worldPosition: {x: 5, y: 8}
    displayLabel: "Level 2 \u2013 Section B (History)"
    isStairNode: 0
    linkedStairNodeID: 
    visualDescription: Shelving with orange spine labels in the 900-999 Dewey range
      (History and Geography). Globe and atlas books visible on the end-cap shelf.
      Grey carpet tiles. Study carrels along the far wall.
  - nodeID: L2_Stairs
    markerName: ImageTarget_L2_Stairs
    floor: 2
    worldPosition: {x: 10, y: 4}
    displayLabel: "Level 2 \u2013 Stairs"
    isStairNode: 1
    linkedStairNodeID: L3_Stairs
    visualDescription: Stairwell opening with metal handrails on both sides. Level
      number signage on the wall. Fire exit door visible nearby. Concrete steps leading
      upward. Yellow fire safety equipment bracket on the wall.
  - nodeID: L3_Stairs
    markerName: ImageTarget_L3_Stairs
    floor: 3
    worldPosition: {x: 10, y: 4}
    displayLabel: "Level 3 \u2013 Stairs Landing"
    isStairNode: 1
    linkedStairNodeID: L2_Stairs
    visualDescription: Top of stairwell landing on the upper floor. Open-plan library
      area visible ahead with lower ceiling than ground floor. Level 3 sign on the
      wall. Natural light from skylights or high windows. Carpet floor.
